ns and government agencies are responsible for over-seeing this usage and management, and how they respond to current environmental concerns. <!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1429002662}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-176716","postID":176716,"title":"Economy and commerce","date":"04\\/14\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/economy-and-commerce\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/14\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Economy and commerce<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-176716 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-economy-and-commerce tag-commerce tag-economy tag-gdp","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/economy-and-commerce\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->The economies of the five LMB countries range from those still developing beyond a reliance on agriculture and natural resources, to more robust export economies supporting themselves and becoming more independent. For the 2015 fiscal year, the World Bank categorized the region\\u2019s economies as \\u201clow-income\\u201d (Cambodia and Myanmar), \\u201clower-middle-income\\u201d (Laos and Vietnam) and \\u201cupper-middle-income\\u201d (Thailand).<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1429002309}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-176713","postID":176713,"title":"Energy","date":"04\\/14\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/energy\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/14\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Energy<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-176713 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-energy","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/energy\\/?lang=en","content":"Photovoltaic cells at Lopburi solar project, Thailand. Photograph: Asian Development Bank, Flickr, 2011. Licensed under Creative Commons Non-Commercial Attribution No-Derivatives 2.0. The demand for energy in South East Asia has increased by two-and-a-half times the global average since 1990, making it one of the most rapid growth rates in the world1. In the context of [&hellip;]","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1429000962}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-179277","postID":179277,"title":"Law and judiciary","date":"04\\/10\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/law-and-judiciary\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/10\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Law and judiciary<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-179277 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-law-and-judiciary tag-human-development tag-social-development tag-social-inclusion","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/law-and-judiciary\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->As a cornerstone of common structures of government, along with executive and legislative branches, the judiciary is of great significance in contributing to the context in which environmental and socioeconomic development occurs.\\n[This page is under development, with additions and updates forthcoming.]<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428645641}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-179098","postID":179098,"title":"Urban administration","date":"04\\/10\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/urban-administration\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/10\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Urban administration<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-179098 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-urban-administration-and-development tag-infrastructure tag-roads tag-social-development tag-transport tag-water","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/urban-administration\\/?lang=en","content":"This page is under development, with additions and updates forthcoming. Traffic police in Phnom Penh, photo by Iwan Gabovitch, 2014. Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution 2.0 Generic &nbsp; The percentage of the total population living in urban areas ranges from 20% in Cambodia to 31% in Vietnam, 32% in Myanmar and 34% in Laos and [&hellip;]","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428641352}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-179089","postID":179089,"title":"Industry","date":"04\\/10\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/industry\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/10\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Industry<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-179089 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-industry-other tag-economy tag-infrastructure tag-roads tag-transport","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/industry\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->The Mekong region holds a vital part of Southeast Asia\\u2019s industrial potential. As defined by Open Development Mekong, the industry category includes not only manufacturing, but also construction and tourism, which are important sources of employment and income in the region.\\n[This page is under development, with additions and updates forthcoming.]<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428639607}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-177470","postID":177470,"title":"Disasters and emergency response","date":"04\\/09\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/disasters-and-emergency-response\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/09\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Disasters and emergency response<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-177470 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-disasters-and-emergency-response tag-aid tag-development tag-environment","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/disasters-and-emergency-response\\/?lang=en","content":"This page is under development, with additions and updates forthcoming. An SH-60F Sea Hawk helicopter surveys a flooded area in Bangkok, 2011. Photo by Jennifer Villalovos. Licensed under Attribution 2.0 Generic. &nbsp; The Mekong region faces its share of natural disasters, especially flooding from the monsoonal rains typical of its climate. Climate change is expected [&hellip;]","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428585311}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-177464","postID":177464,"title":"Land","date":"04\\/09\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/land\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/09\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Land<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-177464 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-land","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/land\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->The ownership and control of land is of critical importance to understanding the Mekong region and its development. A majority of the population is primarily engaged in agriculture, so land is the basis of both residence and livelihood. The five nations encompass a total land area of 1.9 million square kilometers; in geographic size, Myanmar is the largest and Cambodia the smallest.\\n[This page is under development, with additions and updates forthcoming.]<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428581278}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-177457","postID":177457,"title":"Population and census","date":"04\\/09\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/population-and-census\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/09\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Population and census<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-177457 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-population-and-censuses","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/population-and-census\\/?lang=en","content":"This page is under development, with additions and updates forthcoming. A night market in Vietnam. Photgraph: Podoboq, Flickr, 2013. Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution 2.0. Although the Mekong region can be considered as a defined geographic area, it is not a homogenous entity. There is wide variety among the cultures and subcultures of each of [&hellip;]","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428580488}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-177266","postID":177266,"title":"Extractive industries","date":"04\\/09\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/extractive-industries\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/09\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Extractive industries<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-177266 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-extractive-industries","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/extractive-industries\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->Activities related to mining, oil and natural gas have been controversial throughout the Mekong, often bringing powerful corporate interests into conflict with the livelihoods of average citizens. USGS data from 2012 stated that cement, sand, clay, stone and gemstones were produced in all five countries of the Lower Mekong Basin. Regulation of extractive industries in the region is difficult to characterize due to the range of individual cases, but campaigns such as the Extractive Industries Transparency Initiative have made some progress.<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428577656}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-177081","postID":177081,"title":"Government","date":"04\\/09\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/government\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/09\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Government<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-177081 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-government","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/government\\/?lang=en","content":"This page is under development, with additions and updates forthcoming. Presidential palace, Vientiane, Laos. Photograph: caflier002, Flickr. Licensed under Creative Commons Share-Alike 2.0. There are three types of government in the Mekong region: Thailand and Cambodia operate as constitutional monarchies, allowing for royalty and a parliamentary body to coexist. Laos and Vietnam are single-party socialist [&hellip;]","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428575182}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-176906","postID":176906,"title":"Social development","date":"04\\/09\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/social-development\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/09\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Social development<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-176906 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-social-development tag-human-development tag-mdgs tag-social-development tag-social-inclusion","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/social-development\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->Over the last two decades, the countries of the Lower Mekong Basin have all experienced economic development and social transformation. While results are encouraging over all, the improvements across development indicators are not always equal, and as the disparity between the growing urban classes and rural poor increases, and demographic changes continue, inequality in the region still must be addressed.<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428574731}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-174054","postID":174054,"title":"Labor","date":"04\\/08\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/labor\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>04\\/08\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Labor<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-174054 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-labor","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/labor\\/?lang=en","content":"This page is under development, with additions and updates forthcoming. A worker sews a garter to a skirt in a garment factory outside Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Photo by World Bank, Flickr. Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Non-Commercial-No-Derivatives 2.0. Access to suitable and sustainable employment has a direct impact on an individual&rsquo;s livelihood. In the countries of [&hellip;]","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1428488628}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-85432","postID":85432,"title":"Infrastructure","date":"03\\/03\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/infrastructure\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>03\\/03\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Infrastructure<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-85432 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-infrastructure tag-communications tag-infrastructure tag-roads tag-transport","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/infrastructure\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->In the Mekong region, much transportation infrastructure has been built with aid from other nations, particularly China, Japan, and Australia. Greater urbanization and industrialization are driving the increased demand, which Mekong nations are experiencing at relatively high rates, along with rapid population growth. Two recent developments in this sector are the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank created by China in October 2014, and  the US-backed Smart Infrastructure for the Mekong program announced in 2013.<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1425379594}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-61863","postID":61863,"title":"Watersheds","date":"02\\/09\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/watersheds\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>02\\/09\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Watersheds<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-61863 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-environment category-ground-water category-water-environment category-water-pollution tag-soils tag-water tag-watersheds","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/watersheds\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->Watersheds are impacted by many factors, through interaction with both natural elements and human activity in the area. The trees and plants in forests not only tap into the water within the soil, but they also affect the quality and composition of the soil itself, filtering rain water and run off as it flows to streams or down into the water table.<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1423476183}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-61872","postID":61872,"title":"Agriculture and fishing","date":"02\\/09\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/agriculture-and-fishing\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>02\\/09\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Agriculture and fishing<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-61872 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-agriculture-and-fishing tag-agriculture tag-fisheries tag-food-security tag-rice","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/agriculture-and-fishing\\/?lang=en","content":"<!--:en-->The Lower Mekong Basin is moving from largely agrarian fishing and farming countries, to agro-industrial sectors where people farm cash crops rather than those that directly supply their families\\u2019 needs. While there are many crops and food products across the LMB, rice and fish still contribute the most to both their economies and to sustaining their populations.<!--:-->","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1423465918}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-63360","postID":63360,"title":"Open Development Mekong Launched","date":"02\\/06\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/site-update\\/opendevelopment-mekong-launched\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>02\\/06\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Open Development Mekong Launched<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-63360 type-site-update status-publish hentry","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/site-update\\/opendevelopment-mekong-launched\\/?lang=en","content":"Hello world! You should edit me to include your launch announcement text. I would link a blog post in here too!","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1423256886}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-63359","postID":63359,"title":"Example Announcement","date":"02\\/06\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/announcement\\/example-announcement\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>02\\/06\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Example Announcement<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-63359 type-announcement status-publish hentry","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/announcement\\/example-announcement\\/?lang=en","content":"Please delete this after you have added some real annoucements","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1423256797}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-61657","postID":61657,"title":"Hydropower","date":"02\\/06\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/hydropower\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>02\\/06\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Hydropower<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-61657 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-energy category-hydropower-renewable-energy-sources tag-conservation tag-economy tag-electricity tag-energy tag-environment tag-fisheries tag-hydropower tag-natural-resources tag-renewable-energy-sources tag-soils tag-water","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/hydropower\\/?lang=en","content":"The Mekong river system with its vast, complex network of tributaries has been identified as a valuable source of hydroelectricity generation and since the 1960s. The Lower Mekong Basin is a key site for large-scale hydropower dam development1&nbsp;and it is estimated that it has the potential to generate 30,000 megawatts (MW) of hydropower.2 Regional governments [&hellip;]","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1423217421}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-61557","postID":61557,"title":"Mekong River Basin","date":"02\\/06\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/mekong-river-basin\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>02\\/06\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Mekong River Basin<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-61557 type-topic status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry category-environment","permalink":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/mekong-river-basin\\/?lang=en","content":"The Mekong River is the longest river in Southeast Asia, and tenth longest in the world. The river begins its 4,909 Km journey in China, high up in the Tibetan Plateau, replenished by the melting snow of the Himalayas. From here it travels through Myanmar, Laos, Thailand, Cambodia and finally Vietnam, where it joins the [&hellip;]","thumbnail":"","range_slider_property":1423215882}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"id":"post-54156","postID":54156,"title":"Forests and forestry","date":"02\\/03\\/2015","url":"http:\\/\\/odm.dev\\/topics\\/forests-and-forestry\\/?lang=en","bubble":"<small>02\\/03\\/2015<\\/small>\\n<h4>Forests and forestry<\\/h4>","marker":null,"class":"post-54156 t