(10602, 288976, 'rssmi_item_description', 'a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:9:"mystrdate";i:1434035996;s:7:"mytitle";s:68:"Burma Rejects Claims Indian Forces Cross Border in Pursuit of Rebels";s:6:"mylink";s:104:"http://www.irrawaddy.org/burma/burma-rejects-claims-indian-forces-cross-border-in-pursuit-of-rebels.html";s:6:"mydesc";s:2396:"<div><a href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/India.jpg"><img src="http://www.irrawaddy.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/India-1024x731.jpg" alt=" Indian Army soldiers put down the flag-draped coffin of their colleague, who was killed in an attack by tribal separatist guerrillas in India&rsquo;s Manipur state last week. (Photo: Reuters)" width="610" height="435"></a><p>Indian Army soldiers put down the flag-draped coffin of their colleague, who was killed in an attack by tribal separatist guerrillas in India&rsquo;s Manipur state last week. (Photo: Reuters)</p></div>\n<p>RANGOON &mdash; Burma has rejected assertions that Indian armed forces entered the country earlier this week in pursuit of separatists, saying foreign fighters would never be allowed to use Burmese territory to stage attacks.</p>\n<p>India&rsquo;s junior minister for information and broadcasting, Rajyavardhan Singh Rathore, said India&rsquo;s army attacked rebels just over the border with Burma on Tuesday, underlining New Delhi&rsquo;s resolve to fight terrorism beyond the country&rsquo;s borders.</p>\n<p>However a statement from the President&rsquo;s Office in Burma, citing information from troops in the northwest border region, said fighting had only broken out on the Indian side.</p>\n<p>The strike was carried out in response to the killing of 20 Indian soldiers in an ambush in Manipur last week.</p>\n<p>The India army said in a statement that it received intelligence that rebel forces were plotting more attacks.</p>\n<p>The statement from the President&rsquo;s Office denied that any outside forces were using Burma as a staging ground for attacks.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Myanmar will never accept any foreign rebels using its territory and border area as a base,&rdquo; it said. &ldquo;Myanmar is willing to negotiate and cooperate with the Indian government to handle the problem.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>The statement said that India&rsquo;s ambassador to Burma had met with the deputy minister of foreign affairs on Tuesday to &ldquo;explain the situation,&rdquo; but gave no further details.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/burma/burma-rejects-claims-indian-forces-cross-border-in-pursuit-of-rebels.html">Burma Rejects Claims Indian Forces Cross Border in Pursuit of Rebels</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.irrawaddy.org/">The Irrawaddy</a>.</p>";s:7:"myimage";N;s:8:"myAuthor";s:3:"T G";s:12:"itemcategory";s:25:"A_Factiva, Burma, REUTERS";s:7:"mycatid";s:1:"2";s:7:"myGroup";s:13:"The Irrawaddy";s:6:"feedID";i:53149;s:13:"useMediaImage";i:0;}}'),
