(13844, 289702, 'rssmi_item_description', 'a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:9:"mystrdate";i:1434078024;s:7:"mytitle";s:48:"CNRP TV raises $1.5M, abandons share sales model";s:6:"mylink";s:91:"http://www.opendevelopmentcambodia.net/news/cnrp-tv-raises-1-5m-abandons-share-sales-model/";s:6:"mydesc";s:557:"<p>Opposition leader Sam Rainsy said Thursday that he had secured pledges of at least $1.5 million in funding for the opposition&rsquo;s planned television station, but had been forced to abandon a share-selling model to raise the funds.</p>\n<p>A private company created by the CNRP last year received a broadcasting license to begin operating the country&rsquo;s first opposition-run station, and Mr. Rainsy returned Wednesday from a trip to sell $1,000 shares in the company to expatriate supporters of the CNRP in Europe, Canada and the U.S. &hellip;</p>";s:7:"myimage";N;s:8:"myAuthor";s:11:"Ratana Pich";s:12:"itemcategory";s:49:"Cambodia National Rescue Party (CNRP), Sam Rainsy";s:7:"mycatid";N;s:7:"myGroup";N;s:6:"feedID";i:53127;s:13:"useMediaImage";i:0;}}'),
