(19471, 291105, 'rssmi_item_description', 'a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:9:"mystrdate";i:1427894967;s:7:"mytitle";s:16:"Work in Progress";s:6:"mylink";s:42:"http://www.aseannews.net/work-in-progress/";s:6:"mydesc";s:3684:"<p>By Seulki Lee</p>\n<p><strong>BANGKOK, Mar 31&nbsp;</strong> &ndash; &lsquo;WIP (Work in progress)&rsquo;. This is both an easy escape and honest abstract that journalists often hear from ASEAN on community building in the region. Perhaps this is why often, news coverage of ASEAN hardly attracts the readers &ndash; the people of ASEAN &ndash; as there is as yet no &lsquo;news&rsquo;.<span></span></p>\n<p>But discussions at a parallel session of &lsquo;Reporting ASEAN&rsquo; on &lsquo;What Makes A Community?&rsquo; focused on what elements would make up a genuine ASEAN community, with speakers from academic, journalistic and civil society backgrounds.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;ASEAN is founded by leaders of the ASEAN; nations play a big role. What can we do to make ASEAN a better community owned by the people? You just have to feel and see whether you are part of the community or not,&rdquo; said Zeya Thu, deputy chief editor of Myanmar weekly newspaper &lsquo;The Voice&rsquo;.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;When you come to Thailand through the Suvarnabhumi airport at a crowded time, you can quickly pass the ASEAN Lane. You feel you are part of the ASEAN community. But when you are rejected for visa applications to ASEAN countries while American or European can simply get them, then you doubt the community,&rdquo; Zeya added.</p>\n<p>Rosalia Sciortino, an Italian cultural anthropologist and development sociologist who has lived in Southeast Asia for more than two decades, shared her concerns about growing disparities and unsustainable development patterns in the region.</p>\n<p>To create a &lsquo;sharing and caring ASEAN community&rsquo;, Sciortino said five challenges must be addressed &ndash; inclusive growth, sustainable management of natural resources, demographic and health transition with new diseases of the region, the acknowledgement of a plural ASEAN identity, and the protection of vulnerable groups.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;If you look at ASEAN&rsquo;s explanation on the Community, you see all very nice words,&rdquo; said Sciortino. &ldquo;There needs to be a way, (a) mechanism which is structural, not just being (meetings held) every two times a year. there needs to be structure where there is a representation of multi-stakeholder groups.&rsquo;</p>\n<p>In the presentation entitled &lsquo;Quo Vadis, ASEAN Community?&rsquo;, Thai development specialist Apichai Sunchindah highlighted what for him are factors that could undercut the ASEAN community. &ldquo;There are two hidden and silent killers in ASEAN. Transnational Organised Crime (TOC) and high child mortality from preventable causes. &ldquo;We need to get some sense of this,&rdquo; said the former executive director of ASEAN Foundation. &ldquo;Who wins and who loses from the ASEAN Community, we have to talk about this with broad indicators.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;People have to participate and take ownership of ASEAN Community because we have a stake (in it),&rdquo; said Elaine Tan, current executive director of ASEAN Foundation. &ldquo;The ASEAN Foundation is mandated to engage people and ASEAN secretariat. So use the foundation as a vehicle to facilitate your ownership (of the Community),&rdquo; she added.</p>\n<p>A real community should also involve young people. &ldquo;Media should mention the ASEAN youth, two-thirds of the ASEAN population. To engage with them, we have to bring them to get information about this community in the small screen, which they are comfortable with,&rdquo; said Zeya, citing the example of Buzz Feed, a growing social media venue and the source of information for many youngsters today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (END/TAB/JS/SL/15)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>";s:7:"myimage";N;s:8:"myAuthor";s:9:"Admin IPS";s:12:"itemcategory";s:93:"Features, Reporting ASEAN: 2015 and Beyond Series, The ASEAN Beat, aec, asean, ASEAN identity";s:7:"mycatid";N;s:7:"myGroup";N;s:6:"feedID";i:53203;s:13:"useMediaImage";i:0;}}'),
