(291032, 1, '2015-06-13 07:04:03', '2015-06-13 07:04:03', '<!--:en-->The Electoral Integrity Project has just released its annual report, comparing how countries around the world meet international standards.\r\n\r\nA joint project between Harvard University and the University of Sydney, the EIP report gave top marks to Norway, the Czech Republic and South Korea, while Zimbabwe, Belarus and Djibouti fared the worst. [...]\r\n\r\n[Professor Pippa Norris, director of the Electoral Integrity Project, Harvard University]: In particular, in Asia what we have is problems in a number of countries. These have been obviously in the headlines, countries such as Cambodia, such as Thailand, Bangladesh and all of these countries have had violence and street protests. So what we did was we asked a range of experts how they saw the problems in any election. We covered 73 elections in 66 countries during the last 18 months.\r\n\r\nWhat people said was a little surprising. Often when you think why does an election go wrong, people think about the election day, the polls, the votes, and people complain about things like voter fraud, all those being miscounted.\r\n\r\nIn fact, what we found however there was some other problems. For example, money in politics and the issue of political finance was a real issue in many countries, both in Asia and elsewhere. And issues of things like party broadcasts and how far people had a level playing field or how far it was stacked in favour of the government.\r\n\r\nSo there was some hidden problems which I think are really important for agencies trying to strengthen democratic elections.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/international/radio/program/asia-pacific/southeast-asias-electoral-systems-found-wanting/1274536">http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/international/radio/program/asia-pacific/southeast-asias-electoral-systems-found-wanting/1274536</a><!--:-->', '<!--:en-->Southeast Asia''s electoral systems found wanting<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '358-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-13 07:04:03', '2015-06-13 07:04:03', '', 358, 'http://odm.dev/2015/06/13/358-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
